1
00:00:03,871 --> 00:00:09,875
It’s beautiful how devotees
are always aware

2
00:00:09,875 --> 00:00:12,893
of the good fortune 
of other devotees,

3
00:00:13,342 --> 00:00:16,033
[Beauty Cream]

4
00:00:16,633 --> 00:00:21,945
while being always aware of
their own misfortune,

5
00:00:22,049 --> 00:00:24,618
but at this moment, they [women of Mathurā]
realise they're very fortunate.

6
00:00:24,618 --> 00:00:28,937
But their good fortune 
made them think

7
00:00:28,937 --> 00:00:31,816
of the position 
of the Vraja-gopīs.

8
00:00:31,816 --> 00:00:38,491
gopyas tapaḥ kim acaran yad amuṣya rūpaṁ
lāvaṇya-sāram asamordhvam ananya-siddham
 

9
00:00:38,491 --> 00:00:47,603
dṛgbhiḥ pibanty anusavābhinavaṁ durāpam
ekānta-dhāma yaśasaḥ śriya aiśvarasya [SB: 10.44.14].

10
00:00:47,603 --> 00:00:49,347
Gopyas tapaḥ kim: 
what did the gopīs do?

11
00:00:49,347 --> 00:00:52,344
Did they do some kind
of special austerity,

12
00:00:52,344 --> 00:00:57,557
that they get to stare 
with unblinking eyes at Kṛṣṇa?

13
00:00:57,557 --> 00:00:59,320
Forever.

14
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:00,395
Constantly.

15
00:01:00,395 --> 00:01:02,682
We’re just having a glimpse,

16
00:01:04,511 --> 00:01:12,402
just a glimpse of Kṛṣṇa 
has astonished us into thinking,

17
00:01:12,402 --> 00:01:16,069
“What did they do, 
that they’re always with Him?

18
00:01:16,069 --> 00:01:20,016
That He’s always the object
of their vision?”

19
00:01:20,016 --> 00:01:21,627
Kṛṣṇa-mayī.

20
00:01:21,627 --> 00:01:23,542
Devī Kṛṣṇa-mayī.

21
00:01:23,852 --> 00:01:28,690
“Rādhārāṇī,” 
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj saying,

22
00:01:28,690 --> 00:01:36,828
“as if wherever She glances, 
Kṛṣṇa manifests.”

23
00:01:38,812 --> 00:01:44,088
Lāvaṇya-sāram 
asamordhvam ananya-siddham;

24
00:01:44,088 --> 00:01:51,799
So perfect. 
Lāvaṇya-sār means ‘beauty cream’,

25
00:01:51,807 --> 00:01:55,236
but not like in the modern world.

26
00:01:57,945 --> 00:02:05,344
The cream, the crème de la crème, 
of beautiful person,

27
00:02:05,344 --> 00:02:08,787
beautiful form, face.

28
00:02:08,787 --> 00:02:12,542
Madhuraḿ madhuraḿ vapur asya vibhor

29
00:02:17,918 --> 00:02:21,082
… vadanam madhuram,
madhu-gandhi mṛdu-smitam etad aho

30
00:02:21,082 --> 00:02:23,865
madhuraṁ madhuraṁ madhuraṁ madhuram
[Cc: 2.23.35]

31
00:02:23,865 --> 00:02:31,847
Bilvamaṅgala Ṭhākur says, 
“How sweet is Kṛṣṇa?”

32
00:02:31,864 --> 00:02:36,102
“Sweetness personified. 
The form of Kṛṣṇa.”

33
00:02:36,102 --> 00:02:40,304
Viśveṣām anurañjanena 
janayann ānandam indīvara-

34
00:02:40,304 --> 00:02:44,400
śreṇī-śyāmala-komalair upanayann ańgair anańgotsavam
[Cc: 2.8.144].

35
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,563
It’s like a festival,

36
00:02:46,563 --> 00:02:51,244
the form of Kṛṣṇa is like 
a festival for the eyes.

37
00:02:51,310 --> 00:02:53,526
So sweet, so beautiful.

38
00:02:53,526 --> 00:03:02,323
He’s saying, but if you 
focus on Kṛṣṇa’s face,

39
00:03:03,113 --> 00:03:06,105
you’ll see: even sweeter.

40
00:03:06,550 --> 00:03:12,614
And, “Madhu-gandhi mṛdu-smitam etad aho”,

41
00:03:13,738 --> 00:03:17,372
if He smiles,
if there’s a smile on that face,

42
00:03:17,372 --> 00:03:19,309
that’s even sweeter still.

43
00:03:19,309 --> 00:03:24,305
So were going sweet, sweet, 
sweet, sweet, sweeter.

44
00:03:24,747 --> 00:03:29,718
Infinite magnitude 
of sweetness is Kṛṣṇa.

